The paper deals with time synchronization in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The use of distributed algorithms and stochastic approximation techniques suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY). The problem formulation and estimation techniques involve mathematical analysis and optimization, indicating a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.MA).
